# pyenv
#   For a library or package, you might want to ignore these files since the Python version is
#   usually managed by the user. However, for a specific project, you might want to commit these.
# .python-version

# pipenv
#   According to pypa/pipenv#1185, it is recommended to commit Pipfile.lock in version control.
#   However, in cases where the author of a library or package has a 6-tier system of dependency
#   management, it might be useful to ignore it.
#Pipfile.lock

# poetry
#   Similar to Pipenv, see https://python-poetry.org/docs/basic-usage/#commit-your-pyprojecttoml-and-poetrylock-to-git
